After clicking ‘Create Classroom’ the user is taken to this screen. The classroom name field is required while the descri
tion field is optional, and can be edited anytime.

g.text: On clicking Save, the classroom and associated tracks will be created and show up on the classroom view page.

text.tspan: In any given classroom, clicking Create Track will take the user to this view. The user sees fields for track name and
placeholder filled fields for add start/end date/time. This is a fair amount of information, and the user might be
confused by us asking to provide start and end times/dates without knowing why.

g.text: Ideally, the user fills in the name and the other fields and saves.

text.tspan: This is a place where I feel that we need a
teachable moment- why are we asking up
front for start and end dates/times?
Maybe a info icon with a tooltip? A place
where we can say leave the default dates/
times for now, you can always change them
later to look at the analytics more accurately.
An alternate view could be for the user that wants to add multiple tracks on the same page. A toggle/menu option of
single track/multi track is present.
After filling out the first track information, the user wants to add another track. They click the Add another track link and
a new set of fields for another track appear below the first one. Save button moves down.
This could be lower priority for the alpha, if we
get other stuff done, then we could implement
this.
Single/multi track toggle could disappear
entirely, and just have the ‘add another track’
link appear at the bottom by default. How will
the info icon be treated in this case- repeated
with each set of track details??
